    desc="Mana Type: Water"
    status="DRAFT"
><>

<title>Water Mana<>

<content>
    <section> Introduction <>
        <p>Water mana is a type of mana which is harvested the water in the oceans, the rivers and even the rain.
        People who master fire mana can create and command great torrents of water.<>
        <p>Water mana has an affinity with <a t="#mana_*_ice">#<> and <a t="#mana_*_steam">#<>.<>

    <section> Caster Types <>
        <heading level="1">Water Manipulator<>
        <p>Water <a t="#mana_*_manipulators">manipulators<> throws huge wave and cast out gets of water to strike and
        drown their enemies.<>
        <p>In the presence of water, water manipulators can cast even greater water attacks.<>

        <heading level="1">Water Armorers<>
        <p>Water <a t="#mana_*_armorers">armorers<> don't just cover themselves but attempt to create an entire area of
        water, like a giant ball or cube. Within this water, other can't move easily or breathe easily, but the caster
        can move and attack as easily as they could out of water.<>
        <p>In the presence of water, water armorers can create even larger areas to drown out their enemies.<>

        <heading level="1">Water Animators<>
        <p>Water <a t="#mana_*_animators">animators<> can create water elementals to do their bidding. Water elementals
        are reasonably fast, and can't be really damaged by normal physical attacks, and can hit quite hard.<>
        <p>In the presence of water, water animators can create much larger and more effective elementals.<>

        <heading level="1">Water Item Wielders<>
        <p>Water <a t="#mana_*_itemWielders">item wielders<> wield items that emit water on use.
        Examples include the water bow and wave scrolls.<>
<>
